                <note rend="inline" type="source">738.3915/421: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Munro</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-29T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 29, 1931—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>33. The Department is addressing the following telegram to the American Legation
                    at Santo Domingo. Please take action in accordance with the last paragraph
                    thereof.</p>
                <p>[Here follows the text of telegram No. 20, May 29, 2 p.m., to the Minister in the
                    Dominican Republic, printed <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
